This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of face detection using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel feature fusion pyramid and a segmentation branch, which involves the use of supervised learning techniques and attention mechanisms, indicating that it could also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates its model on the WIDER FACE dataset, which is a common benchmark for object detection and recognition, suggesting that it could also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a self-supervised learning approach, which could be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
